<p style="text-align: justify"><img src="/images/UgoRosolia.png" alt="" style="float: left" width="250px" />
I am a postdoctoral scholar at Caltech, working with Prof. <a href="http://www.bipedalrobotics.com/">Aaron Ames</a> and Prof. <a href="http://www.yisongyue.com/">Yisong Yue</a>. My current research focuses on high-level planning in partially observable environments and on designing control algorithms that allow autonomous systems to perform highly dynamical maneuvers while guaranteeing safety.</p>

<p style="text-align: justify">During my PhD at the University of California Berkeley, I worked with Prof. Francesco Borrelli in the <a href="http://www.mpc.berkeley.edu/">MPC lab</a>. I developed the Learning Model Predictive Control (<a href="https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/abstract/document/8039204">LMPC</a>) strategy, which is a model-based policy iteration strategy. This strategy was used to teach an autonomous vehicle how to race!</p>

